  "texts": [
    "The BUSI dataset was used in the metatesting stage to test the performance of the M:jS n ð Þ model obtained by fast adaptation.",
    "For this purpose, all 3 classes were used as the novel set.In the context of meta-learning, splitting datasets into training and testing sets becomes challenging when dealing with datasets like BUSI, which have a small number of classes (normal, benign, and malignant).",
    "In conventional machine learning, we typically split the data into training and testing sets based on individual examples within each class, but in meta-learning, we need to allocate entire classes for training and testing, which can be problematic when dealing with a small number of classes.The BUSI dataset, with its three classes, presents this challenge.",
    "To address it, we employed a cross-domain strategy that involved leveraging two distinct datasets for our meta-learning task.",
    "We used the BreakHis and mini-ImageNet datasets during the meta-training phase."
